It also involves the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as conditional GANs and attentive mechanisms, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of image manipulation techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-category of Multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves the study of facial expressions, which is related to the sub-category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
